Forever your friend,
Courtney xox

Sometimes in life No Matter HOW MUCH You Love someone else, it won't work unless YOU LOVE YOURSELVES 1st... & When someone Doesn't FULLY Love THEMSELVES & Goes into.a Relationship w/this mindset... It's TOXIC, & just gets WORSE & TIRING For ALL Parties Involved & now it may not be Physical/Sexual/Knowingly being Mentally Abusive like behaviors... But IF YOU'RE Knowingly Not Loving/Liking Yourselves & bringing those types of TOXIC emotions into a Relationship, they spill onto Your Parent like you're pour Actual ACID onto them... It'll forever scar them & you...If You don't take care of Your Mental Health, & jump into relationship after relationship thinking He'll... She'll... They'll Solve this, Fix Me & This... In the beginning you feel... Euphoric, like He'll/She'll/They'll FIX ME W/LOVE... RESPECT.... ADORATION... Then the "Newness" of that optimism wears off & You/They/She/He starts to resent, "They didn't fix Me, & Or No... I'm a piece of shit because I Hurt ____ w/my selfish/toxic behaviors".... By saying that...I'm NOT saying Jeffree... & Or Nate are bad People, sometimes OVER LOVING Someone who doesn't LOVE THEMSELVES PROPERLY Is just as TOXIC as Mental/Physical/Sexual Abuse in ways... Now, these are Just my Experiences, PAST & CURRENT... People that don't/won't/Haven't worked through past hurt/traumatic experiences/pain, will VOMIT IT ONTO/INTO EVERY RELATIONSHIP no matter if they're (Platonic/Intimate)...
I hope I worded Everything right, so You & Everyone can Understand what I mean & what I am trying to say, I have ADHD/SEVERE ANXIETY & SEVERE MEMORY ISSUES so sometimes words get jammbled/mixed up... I have a tendency to reword what I've said but it comes out wrong, SORRY 🤦🏻‍♀️😁🤷🏻‍♀️
I hope & pray for Everyones Peace Of Mind & they get the Healing NEEDED & DESERVED to keep on Living Happy, Healthy, Successful Lives... ✌🏻❤️
